WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:03.394
[engine revving]

00:03.568 --> 00:04.656
[barking]

00:04.830 --> 00:07.964
♪ <i>We are driven</i>♪

00:10.662 --> 00:13.622
♪ <i>By the pain</i>♪

00:23.197 --> 00:25.286
ANDRE:
Here we are, killing ourselves

00:25.460 --> 00:27.331
to keep these drugs away,

00:27.505 --> 00:29.072
and our government
is just bringing them in.

00:29.246 --> 00:30.813
I'll make you so much
fucking money, you'll be able

00:30.987 --> 00:32.162
to fund that war
all by yourself.

00:32.336 --> 00:33.859
TEDDY:
You're digging a tunnel.

00:34.034 --> 00:35.600
And it's gonna go all the way
under the border?

00:35.774 --> 00:37.385
All the way.

00:37.559 --> 00:39.822
Little Lee here been fucking
with my crew.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.998
Trying to take our territory.

00:42.172 --> 00:43.521
Yo, I ain't tried.
I took that shit.

00:43.695 --> 00:45.436
You're gonna leave
his people be,

00:45.610 --> 00:47.351
or you're the one that's gonna
find yourself a new plug.

00:47.525 --> 00:49.788
These are the territories
of the people we can trust.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.355
Nobody got no connection
in Inglewood?

00:51.529 --> 00:53.444
Manboy. His sister is
Skully's baby mama.

00:53.618 --> 00:56.099
Okay, okay.

00:56.273 --> 00:57.840
So how much weight we talking?

00:58.014 --> 00:59.450
<i>FRANKLIN: We're making
more money than we ever</i>

00:59.624 --> 01:01.844
<i>could've dreamed of.
What I was wrong</i>

01:02.018 --> 01:04.499
<i>about was the cost.</i>

01:04.673 --> 01:06.544
<i>Lives are gonna be destroyed.</i>

01:06.718 --> 01:08.459
Either Franklin killed Andre,
or he had him killed.

01:08.633 --> 01:09.678
Police ruled it a suicide.

01:09.852 --> 01:12.028
Franklin Saint murdered my dad.

01:14.596 --> 01:15.814
<i>-[gunshot]
-[gasping]</i>

01:15.988 --> 01:17.729
I got you.

01:17.903 --> 01:19.427
<i>LOUIE:
Profits is down.</i>

01:19.601 --> 01:22.386
<i>Violence is rising.
The gang's at war.</i>

01:22.560 --> 01:24.475
This entire business is about
to spin out of control.

01:24.649 --> 01:26.521
No. He is not ready.

01:26.695 --> 01:29.045
It's okay, Mama. I'm here.

01:29.219 --> 01:31.787
<i>TOM BROKAW: There are more than 400 youth gangs in Los Angeles.</i>

01:31.961 --> 01:34.311
<i>And these days, it doesn't
take much to start a gang war.</i>

01:34.485 --> 01:37.184
<i>FRANKLIN:
What I know for sure is,</i>

01:37.358 --> 01:38.620
<i>if we bail,</i>

01:38.794 --> 01:40.535
<i>-there'll be chaos.
-[screaming]</i>

01:40.709 --> 01:44.539
<i>Gangs battling
over control and territory.</i>

01:44.713 --> 01:46.671
<i>And an entire fucking community in ruins.</i>

01:46.845 --> 01:49.021
♪ ♪

01:49.196 --> 01:51.546
<i>I have to stay and fight.</i>

01:55.637 --> 01:57.639
["I Got The..."
by Labi Siffre playing]

02:06.822 --> 02:09.390
♪ ♪

02:09.564 --> 02:11.609
[exhales]

02:28.148 --> 02:33.457
♪ <i>I got the blues,
but I don't mind♪</i>

02:33.631 --> 02:36.460
♪ <i>All I have to do
is get to you♪</i>

02:36.634 --> 02:39.202
♪ <i>And then I feel just fine</i>♪

02:39.376 --> 02:44.555
♪ <i>I'm on a downer,
but not all the way♪</i>

02:44.729 --> 02:47.297
♪ <i>When I'm feelin' low,
you do your thing just so♪</i>

02:47.471 --> 02:50.474
♪ <i>And then I feel okay</i>♪

02:50.648 --> 02:56.088
♪ <i>You're so good,
the way you give♪</i>

02:56.263 --> 03:01.616
♪ <i>You're so good,
you're the best there is♪</i>

03:08.840 --> 03:13.410
♪ <i>I got the blues,
got it oh so bad♪</i>

03:13.584 --> 03:15.804
-♪ <i>When I think of me</i>♪
-Damn.

03:15.978 --> 03:18.285
♪ <i>It's hard to be a person
quite so sad...♪</i>

03:18.459 --> 03:19.808
Hello?

03:19.982 --> 03:21.940
-LOUIE: Hey.
-[chuckles]

03:22.114 --> 03:23.464
[chuckling]:
Hey.

03:23.638 --> 03:25.770
-You come alone?
-Yeah.

03:25.944 --> 03:28.643
Yeah. Peaches--
he, um, gonna grab a bite

03:28.817 --> 03:30.645
-and come back later. Damn!
-Okay.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.342
-[chuckles]
-Look at this place.

03:32.516 --> 03:33.822
Yeah, we still got a little work

03:33.996 --> 03:35.389
to do before Monday,
but come on,

03:35.563 --> 03:36.999
-I got something to show you.
-All right.

03:37.173 --> 03:41.656
Bricks in and out.
Expenses, cash, payroll.

03:41.830 --> 03:45.355
And weekly payouts,
including Nix.

03:45.529 --> 03:48.532
Uh, he been a problem?

03:48.706 --> 03:51.318
Well, he gets his cash
and then stays out the way.

03:52.841 --> 03:55.409
The territories. Okay?

03:55.583 --> 03:57.454
Kilos being moved.

03:57.628 --> 03:59.630
Was steady for a while,
but then the shootings ramped up

03:59.804 --> 04:01.110
and folks got nervous.

04:01.284 --> 04:02.416
You can forget about growth.

04:02.590 --> 04:04.548
We barely
keeping up with the buy.

04:04.722 --> 04:06.420
Plus, more product
coming over the border

04:06.594 --> 04:08.204
means more competition.

04:08.378 --> 04:10.728
The only reason
we got any sense of power

04:10.902 --> 04:13.383
or control is how cheap
we getting Reed's product.

04:13.557 --> 04:17.039
Any change in price or purity,
and we got real problems.

04:17.213 --> 04:18.867
How's it been working with him?

04:19.041 --> 04:20.956
-Who, Reed?
-Mm.

04:21.130 --> 04:23.132
Fine.

04:24.176 --> 04:25.395
All right, cool.

04:25.569 --> 04:27.005
LOUIE:
Mm-hmm.

04:27.179 --> 04:30.357
Well, you ain't making no trips
to Panama.

04:30.531 --> 04:32.228
So where's the cash?

04:32.402 --> 04:34.361
[chuckles softly]
Follow me.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.974
All right, here we go.

04:39.148 --> 04:40.628
There's more at the house.

04:40.802 --> 04:42.717
We're hiding it
every place we can think of.

04:42.891 --> 04:44.936
-[door opens]
-JEROME: Hey, where y'all at?

04:45.110 --> 04:46.938
-Louie!

04:47.112 --> 04:48.940
-Hey.
-[door closes]

04:49.114 --> 04:50.768
What you two motherfuckers
doing lurking around this bitch?

04:50.942 --> 04:52.509
-I'm getting him up to speed.
-Huh?

04:52.683 --> 04:54.206
-Give me a kiss.
-[both chuckle softly]

04:54.381 --> 04:57.035
I want to thank y'all

04:57.209 --> 04:59.299
for keeping this shit going
while I've been hurt.

04:59.473 --> 05:01.910
-I know it ain't been easy.
-JEROME: Easy?

05:02.084 --> 05:03.564
That shit been
downright hazardous.

05:04.565 --> 05:05.783
Ain't exactly smart,

05:05.957 --> 05:08.917
walking into this funeral,
either.

05:10.658 --> 05:13.313
If y'all want to sit
this one out, I understand.

05:18.666 --> 05:20.232
LOUIE:
Come on.

05:20.407 --> 05:22.409
♪ ♪

05:32.636 --> 05:34.595
<i>[buoy bell clanging]</i>

05:37.946 --> 05:39.948
[ship horn blows]

05:44.779 --> 05:46.781
[distant horn blows]

05:51.089 --> 05:52.874
[tires screech]

05:53.048 --> 05:55.050
[vehicle approaching]

06:09.934 --> 06:11.371
[car door closes]

06:11.545 --> 06:13.590
FRANKLIN:
What's up?

06:13.764 --> 06:15.853
-You smoking now?
-TEDDY: Yeah.

06:16.027 --> 06:17.725
Thought maybe
I was getting too healthy.

06:17.899 --> 06:19.944
Who's the new guy?

06:20.118 --> 06:22.164
Lurp. Friend of a friend.

06:22.338 --> 06:24.035
Lurp?

06:24.209 --> 06:26.603
Worked the Long Range
Recon Patrol in Nam.

06:26.777 --> 06:28.344
Name stuck.

06:28.518 --> 06:30.651
Memorable.

06:38.049 --> 06:40.051
[ship horn blows]

06:40.225 --> 06:43.446
You're hiring mercs now?

06:43.620 --> 06:46.406
Can't be too careful, man.

06:46.580 --> 06:48.016
'Cause of what...
what happened to you

06:48.190 --> 06:50.148
or what's happening
to your neighborhood?

06:50.322 --> 06:52.281
Couple gangs at war.

06:52.455 --> 06:54.979
Shit's getting uglier
by the day.

06:55.153 --> 06:56.851
Yeah, I heard.

06:57.025 --> 06:59.331
You know the players?

06:59.506 --> 07:01.508
You try talking sense to 'em?

07:05.381 --> 07:07.339
[women crying softly]

07:07.514 --> 07:09.690
[soft murmuring]

07:18.176 --> 07:20.048
It's Franklin.

07:20.222 --> 07:22.920
Franklin Saint,
your business partner?

07:23.094 --> 07:24.792
How hard you think
it was for them

07:24.966 --> 07:27.447
to get that Jesus nigga
to stay on that cross?

07:28.883 --> 07:30.754
I don't know.

07:30.928 --> 07:34.497
Uh, I, um...
I wanted to come through,

07:34.671 --> 07:38.632
pay my respects,
say I'm sorry for your loss.

07:38.806 --> 07:40.721
I know it ain't
none of my business,

07:40.895 --> 07:42.331
but it seems this shit

07:42.505 --> 07:44.072
between you and Manboy done
got out of hand.

07:44.246 --> 07:47.467
Anything me and mine can do
to help squash that beef

07:47.641 --> 07:49.381
before more people get killed?

07:50.861 --> 07:52.689
<i>MANBOY:
Where y'all just come from,</i>

07:52.863 --> 07:56.301
-a funeral?
-FRANKLIN: Yeah, actually.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.086
-In Inglewood.
-Come at us,

07:58.260 --> 07:59.914
-that's what the fuck happens.
-That's how it started?

08:00.088 --> 08:01.916
-They came at you?
-Of course.

08:02.090 --> 08:03.526
Everybody know Skully crazy.

08:03.700 --> 08:05.702
It's on him.

08:06.790 --> 08:09.489
<i>SKULLY:
Manboy's the fucking problem.</i>

08:09.663 --> 08:13.275
He don't know when
to shut his bitch-ass mouth.

08:13.449 --> 08:15.320
He done fucked up now, though.

08:15.495 --> 08:18.715
I know, and, um,
I know you want to hit back,

08:18.889 --> 08:21.936
but there's got to be a way
to make this right.

08:22.110 --> 08:23.677
[Skully scoffs]

08:23.851 --> 08:25.679
You hear this shit, Khadijah?

08:25.853 --> 08:29.160
This nigga trying to say me
and your brother family,

08:29.334 --> 08:32.294
so we should just kiss
and make up.

08:32.468 --> 08:35.123
I'll tell you what I'm gonna do.

08:35.297 --> 08:38.648
I'm gonna kill every one of them
Compton motherfuckers,

08:38.822 --> 08:42.260
and anybody else
that get in my way.

08:44.219 --> 08:46.656
<i>MANBOY:
I'll tell you this. <i>
They come back at us,</i></i>

08:46.830 --> 08:48.876
you better keep
that formalwear handy,

08:49.050 --> 08:50.573
'cause we'll put every last one
of them niggas

08:50.747 --> 08:52.053
-in the ground.
-[bag thuds]

09:05.370 --> 09:08.417
-That's unfortunate.
-FRANKLIN: Yeah.

09:08.591 --> 09:10.506
You know, I was hoping maybe

09:10.680 --> 09:13.204
you or your people
could help me out with this

09:13.378 --> 09:14.858
before it gets out of hand?

09:16.512 --> 09:18.862
Yeah, you know,

09:19.036 --> 09:21.735
there's things I can help you
with and things I can't.

09:21.909 --> 09:25.129
And unfortunately,
stopping a gang war falls

09:25.303 --> 09:27.349
squarely in the latter.

09:31.832 --> 09:33.877
You know...

09:34.051 --> 09:38.882
in the '50s, the Middle East was
in total chaos.

09:39.056 --> 09:42.407
The Iranians had just
nationalized their oil pipeline

09:42.582 --> 09:44.540
under
General Mohammad Mosaddegh,

09:44.714 --> 09:46.237
and there was concerns

09:46.411 --> 09:48.065
that Mosaddegh might have
communist sympathies,

09:48.239 --> 09:49.763
that he would ultimately

09:49.937 --> 09:51.416
become a puppet
of the Soviet Union,

09:51.591 --> 09:53.505
give the Russians control
of something like 60%

09:53.680 --> 09:55.029
of the free world's
oil reserves.

09:55.203 --> 09:58.989
So, the CIA orchestrated a coup

09:59.163 --> 10:04.125
to replace Mosaddegh
with a general named Zahedi,

10:04.299 --> 10:06.170
and strengthen Shah Pahlavi
in his place.

10:06.344 --> 10:08.303
Now, ultimately,

10:08.477 --> 10:11.785
Shah Pahlavi presented problems
of his own, but...

10:11.959 --> 10:14.570
He was still the lesser
of the two evils.

10:18.574 --> 10:20.924
It was important
that we take action,

10:21.098 --> 10:23.753
back the side that most
benefited us at the time,

10:23.927 --> 10:26.713
try to maintain some measure
of control.

10:26.887 --> 10:29.411
You supply both sides, right?

10:33.894 --> 10:35.199
[sniffs]

10:35.373 --> 10:36.984
Hang in there, kid.

10:51.868 --> 10:53.609
-[phone ringing]
-[indistinct chatter]

10:55.567 --> 10:57.613
Irene Abe.

10:57.787 --> 11:00.660
All right, Chuck.
Tell me something good.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.576
No. No, no.

11:04.751 --> 11:06.448
You said you'd go on the record.

11:06.622 --> 11:08.885
M-My whole story
is based on your...

11:10.278 --> 11:13.107
I-I understand it's scary
to put yourself out there.

11:13.281 --> 11:14.978
But if you don't talk to me,

11:15.152 --> 11:16.980
this is gonna keep happening
to other people,

11:17.154 --> 11:20.767
and trust me, you don't want
that on your conscience. You...

11:22.464 --> 11:25.467
Well, then, fuck you, Chuck,
you coward piece of shit.

11:25.641 --> 11:28.644
The guards at the internment
camp had more spine. Fuck.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.517
WILSON:
Everything okay?

11:34.389 --> 11:36.478
Great. Why?

11:39.133 --> 11:41.091
What's that?
Our marriage certificate?

11:41.265 --> 11:44.791
Uh, Melody Wright.

11:44.965 --> 11:46.444
That girl you were looking for?

11:46.618 --> 11:49.143
The one who went MIA
after her father died?

11:51.145 --> 11:53.147
Oh, Wilson.

11:54.148 --> 11:56.150
You sweet, sweet boy.

11:58.848 --> 12:00.850
All right, I got it.

12:09.946 --> 12:11.992
[Mexican music playing]

12:14.864 --> 12:16.953
[speaks Spanish]
Best in Tijuana.

12:17.127 --> 12:19.564
Just give me the keys.
I'll drive.

12:24.352 --> 12:26.528
What is this?

12:26.702 --> 12:29.531
Cedro gave it to me
for Christmas.

12:29.705 --> 12:32.360
Cedro, he's the younger one?

12:32.534 --> 12:36.059
The-the younger one is Carlito.

12:36.233 --> 12:38.322
Cedro turns six soon.

12:38.496 --> 12:41.021
By the way,

12:41.195 --> 12:42.370
we're gonna have a party.

12:42.544 --> 12:43.937
You should come.

12:44.111 --> 12:46.417
To a six-year-old's
birthday party?

12:46.591 --> 12:48.593
You spend too much time alone,
amigo.

12:48.768 --> 12:51.205
It's not good for you.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.255
I wish you liked baseball.

12:58.429 --> 12:59.996
At least we'd have
something to talk about

13:00.170 --> 13:01.606
on these goddamn drives.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.739
I like Fernando Valenzuela.

13:05.523 --> 13:08.526
You kind of look like
Fernando Valenzuela, actually.

13:08.700 --> 13:10.398
[engine starts]

13:12.052 --> 13:13.357
I'm kidding, calm down.

13:13.531 --> 13:15.577
[siren chirps]

13:17.057 --> 13:19.102
Federales?

13:33.247 --> 13:34.726
[truck door closes]

13:34.901 --> 13:37.251
-GUSTAVO: Michoacán.
-Michoacán?

14:09.718 --> 14:10.937
[scoffs]

14:40.792 --> 14:43.839
[sniffing]

14:52.630 --> 14:54.676
♪ ♪

15:17.133 --> 15:18.874
[crate shatters]

15:29.058 --> 15:31.191
♪ <i>Half past 1:00,
this is how it goes...♪</i>

15:31.365 --> 15:35.195
[indistinct chatter]

15:35.369 --> 15:37.197
FATBACK:
Look at this nigga.

15:37.371 --> 15:39.547
Come on, bruh.

15:39.721 --> 15:42.898
Mr. Saint.
Good to see you out and about.

15:43.072 --> 15:45.248
FRANKLIN:
Mm-hmm.

15:45.422 --> 15:48.077
-He here?
-FATBACK: Yeah.

15:48.251 --> 15:51.254
Come on. What up, Peaches?

15:51.428 --> 15:53.430
♪ <i>And she would do anything
that you want her to♪</i>

15:53.604 --> 15:56.042
♪ <i>She started buggin' out, she <i>didn't care how she looked...</i>♪</i>

15:56.216 --> 15:57.521
[dog barking]

15:57.695 --> 15:59.045
WOMAN:
Oh, yes!

15:59.219 --> 16:00.872
Yes! [moaning]

16:01.047 --> 16:02.613
Yes, Leon!

16:02.787 --> 16:04.789
FRANKLIN:
Know what?
I'm-a come back later.

16:04.964 --> 16:06.878
No, they actually been at it
for a minute.

16:07.053 --> 16:08.010
I think they about done.

16:08.184 --> 16:10.447
-You sure?
-FATBACK: Yeah.

16:10.621 --> 16:13.059
Give me a second.
He'll be glad to get rid of her.

16:14.756 --> 16:17.019
-[knocks on door]
-Hey, Franklin out here.

16:17.193 --> 16:18.803
[indistinct chatter in distance]

16:18.978 --> 16:20.762
[speaking indistinctly]

16:20.936 --> 16:22.982
[plane passing overhead]

16:35.385 --> 16:37.648
Working hard, huh?

16:37.822 --> 16:39.781
If that's work, I'll take it.

16:39.955 --> 16:42.131
Your mama finally let you
out the house, huh?

16:42.305 --> 16:44.003
Kicking and screaming.

16:44.177 --> 16:45.613
You know, she wouldn't
even let us, uh,

16:45.787 --> 16:46.744
come and see you.

16:46.918 --> 16:49.095
Yeah. It's been hard on her.

16:49.269 --> 16:51.271
Yeah.

16:52.446 --> 16:54.622
-Call me?
-We'll see.

17:00.454 --> 17:03.587
Look at you.
[grunts]

17:03.761 --> 17:05.633
Got the projects on lock.

17:07.156 --> 17:09.158
[sighs]
Ladies coming and going.

17:09.332 --> 17:13.119
-Surprised?
-Nah, just saying.

17:13.293 --> 17:15.295
Missed you yesterday, though.

17:15.469 --> 17:17.732
Trying to deal with this
Manboy/Skully shit.

17:17.906 --> 17:19.951
Ain't no dealing
with those motherfuckers.

17:20.126 --> 17:21.475
Only thing you can do
is stay out the way

17:21.649 --> 17:23.172
and be glad they ain't
coming at us.

17:23.346 --> 17:26.610
Yeah, well, that shit
at the Bottoms last week?

17:26.784 --> 17:30.484
Five people were killed,
not one of 'em in the game.

17:31.485 --> 17:34.618
Cost of doing business, homie.

17:34.792 --> 17:37.447
-[helicopter passing overhead]
-We don't do anything soon, man,

17:37.621 --> 17:39.406
it won't just be the Bottoms.

17:39.580 --> 17:41.408
Your neighborhood. Mine.

17:41.582 --> 17:42.800
Our families' lives at risk.

17:42.974 --> 17:44.498
We already there, Saint.

17:44.672 --> 17:45.847
There's too much money
for the taking,

17:46.021 --> 17:47.675
and niggas be too desperate.

17:47.849 --> 17:50.156
What's coming is certain
as Jesus on Sunday, my nigga.

17:52.245 --> 17:54.160
That's why you refuse
to work with Louie?

17:54.334 --> 17:56.553
Lost cause?

17:56.727 --> 18:01.297
Nah. I just ain't get into this
to take orders from your auntie.

18:01.471 --> 18:03.691
I feel you.

18:03.865 --> 18:05.519
But you know I'm back now.

18:05.693 --> 18:08.870
I need you with me, Lee.

18:09.044 --> 18:12.613
I got these projects to manage.
You know, business to run.

18:12.787 --> 18:15.442
I can't leave all that just to
drive you around.

18:15.616 --> 18:19.576
[scoffs]
Drive me around?

18:20.621 --> 18:23.102
I'm good.

18:28.803 --> 18:33.808
You coming to...
Louie's for New Year's?

18:33.982 --> 18:37.290
We'll see.
Might stop by for a minute.

18:41.381 --> 18:43.905
♪ ♪

18:44.079 --> 18:45.602
<i>[cell door clacking]</i>

18:45.776 --> 18:47.778
[chatter in Spanish]

19:18.374 --> 19:21.334
<i>El pocho y el gringo.</i>

19:21.508 --> 19:24.772
Please, have a seat.

19:29.820 --> 19:33.824
Okay.
My name is Oscar Fuentes.

19:33.998 --> 19:36.610
I am the new chief of police
here in Tijuana.

19:36.784 --> 19:39.613
I'm Reed. This is Gustavo.
It's nice to meet you.

19:45.358 --> 19:48.970
Um... I want to start by saying
we were, we were very sorry

19:49.144 --> 19:51.015
to hear about Chief Cala.

19:51.190 --> 19:53.322
The thing was, we s--
we had a-an arrangement

19:53.496 --> 19:54.976
-worked out with him...
-No.

19:55.150 --> 19:57.065
You didn't.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.503
I promise you we did.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.810
Mm, you might have had...

20:02.984 --> 20:07.293
a deal, but... [sighs]

20:07.467 --> 20:09.817
it was not a-a fair one.

20:09.991 --> 20:12.776
-Cala thought it was
pretty fair.
-[Oscar chuckles]

20:12.950 --> 20:16.824
Cala was, uh, small-minded.

20:16.998 --> 20:18.652
Of a different generation.

20:21.176 --> 20:23.700
He didn't fully understand
the scope

20:23.874 --> 20:28.357
of the opportunity ahead
for Tijuana and its people.

20:28.531 --> 20:32.535
Which is why he's not
sitting here today.

20:34.189 --> 20:36.844
Okay. Uh, so if you have
something else in mind,

20:37.018 --> 20:38.541
just let us know.

20:38.715 --> 20:41.196
I'm sure we can find some way
to make you happy.

20:41.370 --> 20:43.894
I really hope so.

20:44.068 --> 20:45.940
Because you're not the only men
moving product

20:46.114 --> 20:48.508
through our plazas.

20:48.682 --> 20:51.250
Maybe, uh...

20:51.424 --> 20:53.208
you've heard about this?

20:57.081 --> 20:58.474
Uh, we have.

20:58.648 --> 21:02.043
The thing is,
I don't see any reason why

21:02.217 --> 21:04.698
our business should have
anything to do with theirs.

21:04.872 --> 21:08.745
Well, I guess that is
another thing

21:08.919 --> 21:12.314
you need me for, isn't it?

21:13.794 --> 21:15.622
Carlos will take you back
to your truck.

21:15.796 --> 21:17.363
There you will find your cargo

21:17.537 --> 21:20.104
in the exact
condition you left it.

21:20.279 --> 21:23.891
Then my men will escort you
to wherever you want to go.

21:24.065 --> 21:26.241
That way, your minds
can be fresh and clear

21:26.415 --> 21:30.724
to think about a fair price
to conduct our business.

21:34.858 --> 21:38.645
He arrested you so they could
go through the truck.

21:38.819 --> 21:41.082
Figure out exactly how much
we're bringing across.

21:41.256 --> 21:43.780
-[train horn blowing]
-What're you going to do?

21:43.954 --> 21:47.262
We pay him.
Whatever he wants.

21:47.436 --> 21:51.092
We can't afford the risk
to say no.

21:52.354 --> 21:53.573
[whistles]

21:55.705 --> 21:57.403
Shit, you see that nigga
walking with that cane?

21:57.577 --> 21:58.752
He look weak as hell, homie.

21:58.926 --> 22:00.536
I'm telling you,

22:00.710 --> 22:02.408
Franklin being back
don't mean shit.

22:02.582 --> 22:06.063
That nigga weak.
He hurt. Soft.

22:06.237 --> 22:08.588
Best not underestimate Saint.

22:08.762 --> 22:12.461
Boy's brain still work.
That's problem enough.

22:12.635 --> 22:14.333
Y'all gonna talk business
all night? Shit.

22:14.507 --> 22:16.770
Damn, Boots, where you
find this one at?

22:16.944 --> 22:18.859
She got it bad, huh?

22:19.033 --> 22:20.774
Shit, she know the goods
when she see it.

22:20.948 --> 22:22.558
-[chuckles softly]
-Sup, girl?

22:22.732 --> 22:23.777
♪ <i>More bass
than a powerful amp...♪</i>

22:23.951 --> 22:25.648
-You should come, too.
-What?

22:25.822 --> 22:28.259
[chuckles softly]
I appreciate the offer,

22:28.434 --> 22:30.349
but I got my hands full.

22:30.523 --> 22:33.003
-Ugh. Uh-uh.
-Next time, though.

22:33.177 --> 22:34.353
I'll see y'all in a minute.

22:34.527 --> 22:36.790
Yeah, a minute sound
about right.

22:36.964 --> 22:39.009
-Bye, sweetie.
-[laughter]

22:39.183 --> 22:42.056
BOOTSY:
Shit, cover your ears, nigga.

22:44.275 --> 22:46.060
Damn.

22:47.104 --> 22:48.932
[Bootsy mutters]

22:49.106 --> 22:50.978
Mm. You ready to have some fun?

22:51.152 --> 22:53.894
Hell yeah, I'm ready.
What you got for me?

22:54.068 --> 22:55.286
I want you to sit right here.

22:55.461 --> 22:56.592
-Right there?
-Mm-hmm.

22:56.766 --> 22:58.333
All right.

23:00.901 --> 23:03.947
-Mm, you like that?
-Shit, you know I do.

23:04.121 --> 23:06.472
Oh. All right.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.652
Do your thing, then.

23:12.826 --> 23:13.914
[zipper opens]

23:14.088 --> 23:16.177
[inhales, moans]

23:20.050 --> 23:24.141
Damn, girl. Mm.

23:24.315 --> 23:25.752
Peekaboo, nigga.

23:28.668 --> 23:30.278
<i>[children laughing, shouting]</i>

23:30.452 --> 23:31.932
WOMAN:
Hey, stop running!

23:44.553 --> 23:47.034
BOY:
Mom!

23:47.208 --> 23:48.557
WOMAN:
Baby?

23:50.080 --> 23:51.430
What's wrong?

23:53.910 --> 23:55.303
Oh, my God.

23:55.477 --> 23:58.001
-[flies buzzing]
-Come on.

23:58.175 --> 24:00.134
Don't look.
Don't look. Come on.

24:00.308 --> 24:01.875
Come on.

24:11.145 --> 24:12.581
You know Manboy gonna
hit back, and you can't

24:12.755 --> 24:15.541
-blame the nigga.
-And people scared.

24:15.715 --> 24:17.151
They ain't trying to be out on
the corners selling right now.

24:17.325 --> 24:19.893
It's fucking up our whole
business.

24:21.372 --> 24:23.418
We pick a side.

24:24.767 --> 24:26.595
Manboy or Skully.

24:26.769 --> 24:28.597
Get one to set the other one up,

24:28.771 --> 24:30.294
ambush 'em,
disappear the bodies,

24:30.469 --> 24:32.079
end this as quick
and as quiet as possible.

24:32.253 --> 24:33.646
You're talking about a massacre.

24:33.820 --> 24:36.257
No. No, I'm talking

24:36.431 --> 24:39.042
about taking a few lives
to save many.

24:39.216 --> 24:41.262
Well, shit.

24:41.436 --> 24:43.656
If we gonna be choosing sides,
then I'm-a take Manboy.

24:45.614 --> 24:47.921
Can't trust Skully
with his crucifixing ass.

24:50.837 --> 24:52.708
Say it.

24:52.882 --> 24:55.102
Okay, I get that Manboy
is the obvious choice.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.582
And I know Skully crazy.

24:56.756 --> 24:58.627
But he always stay in his lane.

24:58.801 --> 25:00.542
"Lane" like
the New Testament type shit?

25:00.716 --> 25:02.544
Manboy always trying to test us,

25:02.718 --> 25:05.112
trying to take a territory,
find a better deal.

25:05.286 --> 25:08.245
He's smart and ambitious
as anybody I ever seen.

25:08.419 --> 25:09.769
We back him?

25:09.943 --> 25:12.119
When he done with Skully,
we next.

25:16.863 --> 25:18.386
[heavy door rattling]

25:30.790 --> 25:33.967
Hey, you can crash here
if you don't want to drive back.

25:35.795 --> 25:37.797
Nuvia makes menudo.

25:44.717 --> 25:46.893
[Teddy coughs]

25:47.067 --> 25:50.070
<i>MAN [on TV]: The level of violence seen <i>in that era pales in comparison</i></i>

25:50.244 --> 25:53.682
<i>to the carnage seen in cities
all across America today.</i>

25:53.856 --> 25:57.643
<i>In the past, organized crime bosses introduced tight control</i>

25:57.817 --> 25:59.688
<i>and enforced ground rules.</i>

25:59.862 --> 26:01.734
<i>Civilian deaths
were to be avoided</i>

26:01.908 --> 26:04.214
<i>and every attempt was made
to not kill</i>

26:04.388 --> 26:07.696
<i>law enforcement officers.
Today, some places...</i>

26:07.870 --> 26:09.829
