26:33.243 --> 26:35.811
♪ <i>No, you can't stop the clock</i>♪

26:35.985 --> 26:38.771
♪ <i>No, you can't stop
the clock...♪</i>

26:38.945 --> 26:41.034
[pager beeping]

26:41.208 --> 26:43.036
[sighs]

26:44.907 --> 26:46.953
It's McDonald.

26:47.127 --> 26:48.607
[turns page]

26:50.347 --> 26:52.611
Uh, sorry, you're saying...
you're saying that, uh,

26:52.785 --> 26:54.961
they-they didn't arrive
in Panama City,

26:55.135 --> 26:57.877
or that they didn't arrive
at-at the airstrip?

26:58.051 --> 27:00.053
[clears throat]

27:02.098 --> 27:04.013
Yeah, just let me...
let me get into it, and then

27:04.187 --> 27:06.581
I'll-I'll-I'll get you back
at this number.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.716
Okay, thanks.

27:18.071 --> 27:20.073
[line ringing]

27:27.994 --> 27:30.649
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE [over phone]:
Please leave a message <i>
after the tone.</i></i>

27:30.823 --> 27:32.912
-[beeps]
-Hey, Avi, it's Reed Thompson.

27:33.086 --> 27:35.349
Listen, my contact
in Costa Rica said

27:35.523 --> 27:37.220
that the cargo
never even showed up.

27:37.394 --> 27:39.396
So please give me a call back at
this number as soon as you can.

27:39.570 --> 27:41.355
Thank you.

27:50.625 --> 27:52.671
[indistinct chatter]

27:53.846 --> 27:55.848
[grunts]

28:02.942 --> 28:04.944
[hip-hop music playing faintly]

28:13.692 --> 28:16.564
Probably best I go alone.

28:16.738 --> 28:19.001
I doubt it.

28:24.877 --> 28:26.356
All right.

28:39.848 --> 28:41.545
CORNROWS:
Yo!

28:56.735 --> 28:58.737
[door closes]

29:00.347 --> 29:02.349
-[mutters]
-[baby crying]

29:05.004 --> 29:07.963
[chuckles]

29:08.137 --> 29:09.878
[indistinct chatter]

29:23.936 --> 29:26.329
KHADIJAH:
You put conditioner in it first?

29:26.503 --> 29:29.550
[scoffs] I'm telling you, it'll
make it a whole lot easier.

29:29.724 --> 29:30.943
[knocking on door]

29:32.379 --> 29:33.772
You gonna want
to see this shit, blood.

29:37.384 --> 29:39.342
SKULLY:
Hey, Khadijah!

29:39.516 --> 29:41.562
-Go with Mom.
-KHADIJAH: Come on.

29:43.216 --> 29:46.045
SKULLY:
That don't look like no re-up.

29:52.834 --> 29:54.053
Goddamn.

29:56.533 --> 29:58.405
I got to sit down.

30:01.582 --> 30:04.759
Thank you.
[grunts]

30:04.933 --> 30:08.110
It's a Dragunov.

30:08.284 --> 30:11.113
Accurate from half a mile away.

30:11.287 --> 30:14.247
Ten rounds per mag,
telescopic scope.

30:14.421 --> 30:16.902
One of these once took down
an airplane.

30:17.076 --> 30:19.165
So what's the deal, youngblood?

30:19.339 --> 30:22.777
Deal is I want this war
between you and Manboy done.

30:23.778 --> 30:26.041
Decided to help you finish it.

30:26.215 --> 30:28.478
You said it yourself, right?

30:28.652 --> 30:31.612
Manboy don't respect shit.

30:31.786 --> 30:34.702
He wants power, territory.
You've been loyal.

30:34.876 --> 30:36.443
Got the soldiers
to do this shit.

30:38.097 --> 30:40.142
All you need is a little help.

30:43.276 --> 30:46.105
[exhales]
You feel that?

30:47.715 --> 30:49.978
Hell yeah, I feel that.

30:51.023 --> 30:52.807
Feel like a nigga back
in the pen, and somebody

30:52.981 --> 30:55.331
in the shower trying
to sneak up behind a nigga.

30:55.505 --> 30:57.246
CORNROWS:
Mm-hmm. Exactly.

30:57.420 --> 30:59.292
SKULLY:
What about you, Khadijah?

30:59.466 --> 31:01.947
You feel like
you about to get fucked?

31:02.121 --> 31:05.646
Yep. Both holes.

31:08.997 --> 31:11.173
That's fine.

31:11.347 --> 31:12.827
You don't want my help,
it's fine.

31:13.001 --> 31:14.873
Keep shooting it out,
trading losses.

31:15.047 --> 31:17.484
[zipper closes]

31:18.833 --> 31:21.140
How many can you get?

31:23.272 --> 31:25.622
As many as you want.

31:25.796 --> 31:27.842
Uzis, too.

31:30.018 --> 31:31.933
From who?

31:32.107 --> 31:33.195
Israeli.

31:33.369 --> 31:35.154
He legit. It's where I get mine.

31:35.328 --> 31:37.852
-How much?
-Dragunovs are two G's.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.115
Uzis are $600. More than fair.

31:40.289 --> 31:43.031
Come with me if you want,
meet him.

31:43.205 --> 31:44.815
You don't like what you see,
walk away.

31:44.990 --> 31:46.905
No hard feelings.

31:47.079 --> 31:48.863
-You gonna be there?
-Of course, yeah.

31:49.037 --> 31:50.473
I just want this done, man,

31:50.647 --> 31:52.954
so we can get back
to making that money.

31:53.128 --> 31:55.261
Man, if you trying to play me,

31:55.435 --> 31:58.873
I'm-a send every nigga I got
to fuck your world up.

31:59.830 --> 32:01.571
You feel me?

32:03.573 --> 32:06.750
Yeah. Yeah, I feel you.

32:08.535 --> 32:10.537
<i>ANNOUNCER [over radio]:
Draws a foul on <i>
the penetration move.</i></i>

32:10.711 --> 32:13.366
<i>Great first step.
As you can see there...</i>

32:15.716 --> 32:17.631
What's up, Drew?

32:17.805 --> 32:19.415
Saint.

32:24.855 --> 32:27.206
Listen, man,
I'm sorry about Bootsy.

32:28.729 --> 32:31.079
Ain't right,
what they did to him.

32:33.864 --> 32:36.041
I think it's time
for Skully to go.

32:36.215 --> 32:38.086
[scoffs]
You think?

32:38.260 --> 32:40.567
Mm-hmm.

32:40.741 --> 32:42.438
I want to help you out.

32:42.612 --> 32:44.397
Don't need your help.

32:44.571 --> 32:46.790
I just came
from the Bottoms, man.

32:46.965 --> 32:49.228
They got an army
waiting for y'all to show up.

32:49.402 --> 32:51.882
Trust me, you need my help.

32:52.057 --> 32:54.407
And how you gonna do that?

32:54.581 --> 32:56.583
[exhales]

32:58.106 --> 33:00.152
[grunts]

33:00.326 --> 33:03.242
See, the thing is,
Skully still buys from me.

33:03.416 --> 33:05.461
He trusts me.

33:05.635 --> 33:08.769
I'll draw out him and his folks,
and you'll ambush 'em.

33:08.943 --> 33:13.252
With Skully gone,
Inglewood will be in chaos.

33:13.426 --> 33:15.689
And I'll bleed them dry.

33:15.863 --> 33:17.517
No more cocaine.

33:18.648 --> 33:20.824
It'll be worse for a minute.

33:20.999 --> 33:23.131
In the long run,
we'll all be better off.

33:23.305 --> 33:25.090
And you'll get revenge
for Bootsy.

33:26.134 --> 33:27.266
Hmm?

33:29.137 --> 33:31.313
How the fuck I know
you ain't trying to play me?

33:31.487 --> 33:33.576
You don't.

33:33.750 --> 33:37.450
But take a ride with me.
I'll show you.

33:45.980 --> 33:48.113
[seabirds screeching]

33:48.287 --> 33:50.376
[music playing faintly]

33:50.550 --> 33:52.987
[door opens]

33:53.161 --> 33:55.120
<i>Opa,</i>Avi.

33:56.295 --> 33:58.297
[speaks Hebrew]

34:01.822 --> 34:03.519
Wow. And here I was,
thinking maybe

34:03.693 --> 34:06.348
I was gonna have to find myself
a new arms dealer.

34:06.522 --> 34:08.133
My apologies.

34:08.307 --> 34:10.700
Argentina isn't the easiest
place to keep in touch.

34:10.874 --> 34:12.615
Jesus, man, don't tell me
you were on vacation

34:12.789 --> 34:14.487
while I got people dying
and guns missing.

34:14.661 --> 34:16.793
Of course not.

34:16.967 --> 34:18.404
We were hunting Nazis.

34:18.578 --> 34:20.536
You're what?

34:20.710 --> 34:24.975
We got a tip Josef Schwammberger
is hiding out near Catamarca.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.456
You know his work?

34:27.630 --> 34:30.155
He was in charge
of three death camps in Poland.

34:30.329 --> 34:32.853
Executed hundreds.

34:33.027 --> 34:35.551
Women, children.

34:35.725 --> 34:37.379
Oh, he's serious.

34:37.553 --> 34:38.989
AVI:
I'm always serious
when it comes down

34:39.164 --> 34:41.514
to the greatest enemy the Jewish
people has ever known.

34:42.906 --> 34:45.387
Don't you want to know
if we got him?

34:45.561 --> 34:47.607
Currently, I'm a little more
concerned about those guns.

34:49.261 --> 34:51.437
Yeah, well,
I don't know quite yet,

34:51.611 --> 34:54.048
but we're working on it.

34:54.222 --> 34:56.442
Do you know how difficult
and complicated

34:56.616 --> 34:59.706
the international arms game is?

34:59.880 --> 35:02.317
It's a miracle anything
ever goes through.

35:02.491 --> 35:05.059
No, I-I know exactly how
complicated it is.

35:05.233 --> 35:07.105
But, you know, Avi,
that's the reason

35:07.279 --> 35:09.542
that I pay you the exorbitant
sums of money that I do

35:09.716 --> 35:11.196
is so that when things go wrong,
I can trust

35:11.370 --> 35:12.371
that you're there to fix them.

35:12.545 --> 35:14.155
That is your job.

35:14.329 --> 35:16.897
Listen, I'm sending Lior
on the next plane to Panama.

35:17.071 --> 35:19.726
Okay? We'll find out
what happened.

35:19.900 --> 35:22.381
I also need you on that flight
to Panama.

35:22.555 --> 35:24.078
I'd like for you
to find out yourself.

35:24.252 --> 35:27.386
[laughing]

35:27.560 --> 35:29.779
I trust Lior with my life.

35:29.953 --> 35:33.000
-Don't worry, he'll find out.
-I'm not worried.
I just don't want Lior

35:33.174 --> 35:35.437
-fixing your problems for you.
-Are you saying that I can't
handle myself?

35:35.611 --> 35:37.135
I don't even know
who the fuck you are, man.

35:37.309 --> 35:38.919
-It's okay, Lior.
-LIOR: Hey, if he has something

35:39.093 --> 35:40.616
-to say, let him say it.
-I did say something, and for

35:40.790 --> 35:41.574
-some reason,
this guy keeps talking.
-Shut up, you.

35:41.748 --> 35:42.575
What the fuck?

35:42.749 --> 35:43.837
I just don't understand

35:44.011 --> 35:45.882
-what his problem is.
-Okay.

35:46.056 --> 35:47.928
-It's fine. I'll go. All right?
-LIOR: Why? What's his problem?

35:48.102 --> 35:49.495
-Hey.
-My problem is that you
don't seem to hear too well.

35:49.669 --> 35:51.888
-I hear fucking excellent...
-Fuck.

35:52.062 --> 35:54.761
Fuck, man!

35:54.935 --> 35:56.589
-[Lior groaning]
-You hear perfectly fine now?

35:58.286 --> 36:00.332
Okay.

36:00.506 --> 36:02.421
The fuck, man?

36:02.595 --> 36:04.423
What the fuck is wrong with you?

36:06.686 --> 36:09.645
TEDDY:
I just don't know how much
more clear I can make myself.

36:09.819 --> 36:12.431
I need to know where my guns are
and I want you to find out.

36:12.605 --> 36:15.608
And you'll let me know
as soon as you do.

36:22.963 --> 36:25.095
<i>DICK CLARK: And we're having a good time...</i>

36:25.270 --> 36:26.793
-CISSY: You can blow on it
all you want to.
-ALTON: I've got to get it

36:26.967 --> 36:28.969
working.
I got to get it working.

36:29.143 --> 36:31.450
-Well, you-- Can you get
it working, please? Ooh!
-[Alton grunts]

36:31.624 --> 36:33.147
-CISSY: Ten.
-Who's winning?

36:33.321 --> 36:34.975
ALTON:
[stammers] Who do you think?

36:35.149 --> 36:37.325
Never play Monopoly with
an aspiring real estate mogul.

36:37.499 --> 36:39.327
-[Franklin chuckles]
-CISSY: Thank you.

36:39.501 --> 36:40.807
Thank you very much.

36:40.981 --> 36:42.504
Where's your cane?

36:42.678 --> 36:44.941
Oh. Thought I'd go without it.

36:45.115 --> 36:47.161
Well, now, uh...

36:47.335 --> 36:48.771
think that's wise?

36:48.945 --> 36:51.034
I'm thinking it'd be nice
for just one night

36:51.209 --> 36:53.341
to not have everybody looking
at me like I got something

36:53.515 --> 36:55.169
-wrong with me.
-You do have something
wrong with you.

36:55.343 --> 36:57.650
-ALTON: Come on.
-CISSY: What?

36:59.347 --> 37:02.002
Listen, I want y'all
to come with me tonight.

37:05.005 --> 37:07.094
New year, fresh start.

37:07.268 --> 37:10.184
Jerome and Louie would love it.

37:11.881 --> 37:14.144
Y'all can finally
bury the hatchet,

37:14.319 --> 37:17.409
so we can get back
to being a family.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.327
Just keep yourself safe, son.

37:22.501 --> 37:24.503
[door closes]

37:27.854 --> 37:30.683
Ready whenever you are, sir.

37:32.859 --> 37:34.208
[exhales]

37:34.382 --> 37:37.167
All right.

37:37.342 --> 37:39.344
[grunts]

37:41.868 --> 37:43.435
Love you.

37:43.609 --> 37:46.089
FRANKLIN:
I love you, too.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.004
Happy New Year.

37:48.178 --> 37:49.919
All right.

37:50.093 --> 37:52.095
["Flash Light"
by Parliament playing]

37:54.707 --> 37:58.232
♪ <i>Now, I lay me down to sleep</i>♪

37:58.406 --> 38:00.713
♪ <i>Ooh</i>♪

38:00.887 --> 38:03.106
♪ <i>I just can't find a beat...</i>♪

38:03.281 --> 38:04.630
FRANKLIN:
El Oso!

38:04.804 --> 38:06.719
Happy New Year, man.

38:06.893 --> 38:08.460
Thank you for the invitation.

38:08.634 --> 38:10.636
Yeah.
The past is the past, right?

38:10.810 --> 38:12.594
-Time to move on. <i>
-Orale.</i>

38:12.768 --> 38:15.815
Congratulations, the place
is fucking amazing.

38:15.989 --> 38:17.599
Thanks, Reed.

38:17.773 --> 38:20.298
Let me show you around.

38:20.472 --> 38:22.387
Ain't that that girl Tanosse
from back in the day?

38:22.561 --> 38:24.563
FRANKLIN:
Yeah.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.741
Mm-hmm, that's the one you got
your first nut from.

38:28.915 --> 38:31.439
Mm-hmm. [chuckles]

38:31.613 --> 38:33.746
You want a drink,
tequila or something?

38:33.920 --> 38:35.878
-Water?
-Water. Two waters, please.

38:36.052 --> 38:38.054
♪ <i>Listen, listen,
listen for the beatbox♪</i>

38:38.228 --> 38:39.229
♪ <i>Huh!</i>♪

38:39.404 --> 38:41.144
♪ <i>Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha</i>♪

38:41.319 --> 38:43.582
♪ <i>Yup, baby, yup, baby,
yup, baby♪</i>

38:43.756 --> 38:46.454
♪ <i>Come on, everybody, hurry up</i>♪

38:46.628 --> 38:48.674
♪ <i>Clap, clap, clap, come on...</i>♪

38:48.848 --> 38:50.632
Oh. Hi.

38:51.720 --> 38:53.896
Guess I shouldn't be surprised,
seeing you here.

38:54.070 --> 38:56.464
No? Why's that?

38:56.638 --> 38:59.032
'Cause you was always the girl
who knew everyone.

38:59.206 --> 39:01.426
Always in the right place,
right time.

39:01.600 --> 39:03.645
And that's what this is?

39:03.819 --> 39:05.430
-The right place?
-♪ <i>Everybody say ho!</i>♪

39:05.604 --> 39:06.909
♪ <i>Ho!</i>♪

39:07.083 --> 39:09.042
It is tonight.

39:09.216 --> 39:10.435
♪ <i>Now everybody scream</i>♪

39:10.609 --> 39:12.524
How you doing, T?

39:12.698 --> 39:13.916
I'm good.

39:14.090 --> 39:15.091
You look it.

39:15.265 --> 39:16.963
So do you.

39:17.137 --> 39:18.791
But I heard some things.

39:20.662 --> 39:22.229
Like what?

39:22.403 --> 39:25.014
Like the kid who was prep school
bound took three bullets.

39:26.581 --> 39:29.149
Never thought it'd be you
in this game.

39:29.323 --> 39:30.629
I didn't like the alternative.

39:30.803 --> 39:32.631
Which was what?

39:32.805 --> 39:34.894
Their rules.

39:35.068 --> 39:37.462
-♪ <i>Make it go uh</i>♪
-♪ <i>Uh</i>♪

39:37.636 --> 39:38.898
♪ <i>Nah-nah-nah-nah...</i>♪

39:39.072 --> 39:42.380
-I remember him.
-Who, Leon?

39:42.554 --> 39:44.033
♪ <i>Nah-nah-nah-nah...</i>♪

39:44.207 --> 39:45.992
Glad to see y'all still cool.

39:46.166 --> 39:49.735
It's important to keep
them real niggas around.

39:49.909 --> 39:52.694
The ones who was riding
before you came up, right?

39:52.868 --> 39:54.217
-Mm.
-LEON: Hey!

39:54.392 --> 39:56.350
Hey, what the fuck
you doing here?!

39:56.524 --> 39:58.352
♪ <i>No matter what the age...</i>♪

39:58.526 --> 39:59.614
I asked you a question.
Why the fuck you here?!

39:59.788 --> 40:02.008
Leon, do not make a scene.

40:02.182 --> 40:03.401
I was invited.

40:03.575 --> 40:05.446
By who?

40:05.620 --> 40:08.057
-By the family.
-Hey, hey, now. Come on.

40:08.231 --> 40:09.494
Let's not do this here.

40:09.668 --> 40:10.408
Let's get it off the floor,
come on.

40:10.582 --> 40:13.280
Come on, baby.

40:13.454 --> 40:15.891
♪ <i>Nah-nah-nah-nah,
it'll make you go...♪</i>

40:16.065 --> 40:18.633
I got to remind you what this
motherfucker responsible for?

40:18.807 --> 40:21.723
-Leon, you need
to calm the fuck down.
-Kevin dead because of them.

40:21.897 --> 40:23.421
FRANKLIN:
Kevin's dead because
he didn't listen.

40:23.595 --> 40:25.988
-No, fuck that!
-Leon!
-The fuck are you doing?

40:26.162 --> 40:28.121
-Franklin, please get control
of your man.
-Hey, you stay out of it.

40:28.295 --> 40:29.862
LEON:
They went behind our back.
They went to Kevin,

40:30.036 --> 40:31.777
offered him Conejo
for that motherfucking recipe.

40:31.951 --> 40:33.561
-FRANKLIN: I don't need
a history lesson.
-Then how the hell

40:33.735 --> 40:35.215
you gonna do business with him
like nothing happened?!

40:35.389 --> 40:37.217
We've been doing business
with him, for months!

40:37.391 --> 40:38.653
And you'd know that
if you'd been around!

40:38.827 --> 40:40.350
Who the fuck you talking to?!

40:40.525 --> 40:42.483
When you went down,
what do you think happened?

40:42.657 --> 40:44.877
Everybody came at us,
trying to take our territory

40:45.051 --> 40:46.966
and fuck us up.
Who you think kept 'em back?

40:47.140 --> 40:49.142
Louie?
Jerome and his fucking speakers?

40:49.316 --> 40:52.319
It was me and my
motherfucking crew, nigga.

40:52.493 --> 40:54.234
And instead of gratitude, you
want me to embrace this nigga?

40:54.408 --> 40:56.584
-Put the gun down!
-Louie, shut the fuck up!

40:56.758 --> 40:58.847
-Hey, hey, now watch
your mouth now.
-Hey, back up off him, nigga.

40:59.021 --> 41:01.067
-I'll beat your fat ass.
-Leon, this is about
business. Huh?

41:01.241 --> 41:03.112
-Business.
-No, it's about what's right.

41:05.245 --> 41:07.290
Lower it.

41:14.472 --> 41:17.605
Reed, Oso, leave now.

41:26.832 --> 41:28.834
[Leon panting]

41:33.708 --> 41:35.710
You lost, you know that?

41:35.884 --> 41:37.973
Money's got your head
all fucked up.

41:38.147 --> 41:40.585
Or maybe your head was
never right to begin with.

41:40.759 --> 41:42.238
You know, I thought
with me being hurt, maybe

41:42.412 --> 41:44.589
you'd grow up, stop acting
like a fucking child!

41:44.763 --> 41:46.547
-Nigga, fuck you!
-Fuck me?!

41:46.721 --> 41:49.158
You know what, you're gonna
get yourself killed, man.

41:49.332 --> 41:50.682
And I ain't gonna lay in bed
at night thinking I ain't try

41:50.856 --> 41:52.292
to set your stupid ass straight!

41:52.466 --> 41:54.076
You ain't got to worry
about me, nigga,

41:54.250 --> 41:55.600
-'cause I'm done with your ass!
-Fine!

41:55.774 --> 41:58.211
Find your own fucking plug then.

41:58.385 --> 42:00.474
Do shit the way you want.

42:03.129 --> 42:05.566
You just stay
the fuck out my way.

42:05.740 --> 42:07.786
[grunts softly]

42:09.483 --> 42:12.181
Stupid motherfucker.

42:12.355 --> 42:14.357
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Come on now, nephew.

42:27.240 --> 42:29.634
[birds chirping]

42:29.808 --> 42:31.810
[children shouting playfully]

42:44.344 --> 42:46.520
<i>[knocking on door]</i>

42:47.521 --> 42:49.915
-Bernice Wright?
-Yes.

42:50.089 --> 42:51.481
Uh, I'm Irene Abe.

42:51.656 --> 42:52.657
I'm a reporter
with the <i>Herald Examiner.</i>

42:52.831 --> 42:54.833
The <i>Herald?</i>In Odessa?

42:55.007 --> 42:56.791
No, ma'am. In Los Angeles.

42:56.965 --> 42:59.185
Your brother was Sergeant Andre
Wright, LAPD, is that right?

42:59.359 --> 43:00.926
I don't want to talk
about any of this.

43:01.100 --> 43:02.536
I drove a long way
to come see you.

43:02.710 --> 43:03.929
Well, I'm afraid
you've wasted your time.

43:04.103 --> 43:05.408
Please. I just need five minutes

43:05.583 --> 43:06.496
of your time and then I'll go.

43:06.671 --> 43:08.673
It's okay, Aunt Bernice.

43:10.239 --> 43:12.546
You can let her in.

43:14.853 --> 43:16.202
[sighs]

43:18.073 --> 43:20.075
I appreciate
you inviting me in, Melody.

43:20.249 --> 43:21.686
I know you've been
through a lot,

43:21.860 --> 43:23.557
and I'm not here
to cause more problems.

43:23.731 --> 43:25.254
MELODY:
It doesn't matter.

43:25.428 --> 43:27.996
The Lord's justice will be
served as He sees fit.

43:28.170 --> 43:31.173
All we can do is
be pure of heart in His gaze.

43:31.347 --> 43:32.958
Amen.

43:33.132 --> 43:35.395
Uh, I covered what happened

43:35.569 --> 43:37.179
-to your father.
-[pen clicks]

43:37.353 --> 43:39.747
I'm also aware
of what took place a week later,

43:39.921 --> 43:41.009
when your neighbor Franklin
was shot.

43:41.183 --> 43:42.228
Melody didn't have nothing

43:42.402 --> 43:44.056
to do with any of that.

43:44.230 --> 43:46.536
Franklin said he didn't
know who did it, right?

43:46.711 --> 43:48.930
I-I'm not saying she did.

43:49.104 --> 43:51.933
But there are questions
that still need to be answered.

43:52.107 --> 43:54.675
Why your father did what he did.

43:54.849 --> 43:58.070
Who shot Franklin and why.

43:58.244 --> 44:01.073
Why do you care about all this?

44:01.247 --> 44:03.728
About my daddy and Franklin.

44:04.903 --> 44:07.427
Because no one else seems to.

44:07.601 --> 44:10.212
I was born
in the Crenshaw District.

44:10.386 --> 44:12.084
Grew up there.

44:12.258 --> 44:14.260
Raised my own daughter there.

44:16.088 --> 44:18.960
I'm watching it change,
almost by the day.

44:19.134 --> 44:22.485
I'm scared,
because I don't understand why.

44:22.660 --> 44:25.445
And I think you do.

44:26.446 --> 44:28.143
If you can help me,

44:28.317 --> 44:31.320
I can tell the story,
and telling the story will make

44:31.494 --> 44:33.975
-people pay attention.
-It's not your place to try
and stop what the Lord intends.

44:34.149 --> 44:36.195
All due respect, Melody,

44:36.369 --> 44:39.111
the Lord didn't break Watergate.
Woodward and Bernstein did.

44:39.285 --> 44:40.765
Of course He did.

44:40.939 --> 44:42.767
He guided them.

44:42.941 --> 44:45.073
Just as He will

44:45.247 --> 44:46.988
or won't

44:47.162 --> 44:49.164
guide you.

44:50.600 --> 44:52.298
[stammers]

44:52.472 --> 44:55.605
Maybe the Lord
sent me here to you.

44:55.780 --> 44:58.565
So you can tell me
what really happened.

44:58.739 --> 45:01.133
How's it go?

45:01.307 --> 45:04.223
The truth will set you free?

45:11.796 --> 45:13.623
♪ ♪

45:13.798 --> 45:15.800
[distant siren wailing]

45:17.715 --> 45:19.717
[pills rattling]

45:32.251 --> 45:34.340
[groans]

45:35.733 --> 45:38.736
MANBOY:
These motherfuckers
killed Bootsy.

45:38.910 --> 45:41.477
Put that nigga on a cross.

45:41.651 --> 45:44.524
It's time to show these
motherfuckers what time it is.

45:47.527 --> 45:49.529
Let's roll.

45:50.530 --> 45:52.532
[labored breathing]

46:03.238 --> 46:05.240
♪ ♪

46:24.564 --> 46:26.566
ALTON:
Heading out?

46:27.697 --> 46:29.830
[sighs] Uh, yeah.

46:30.004 --> 46:32.398
Just gonna get a bite with Lurp.

46:33.747 --> 46:36.271
Late-night craving, huh?

46:36.445 --> 46:38.012
Yeah.

46:38.186 --> 46:41.102
Uh-huh.
And is that a .38

46:41.276 --> 46:43.235
or a .45 you got in your waist?

46:45.411 --> 46:47.587
You know, I was thinking

46:47.761 --> 46:50.242
about putting that VCR to use.

46:50.416 --> 46:53.767
Tossing in one of those
new tapes, like

46:53.941 --> 46:55.943
<i>Enter the Dragon.</i>

47:01.035 --> 47:02.558
Remember how many times
you made me

47:02.732 --> 47:05.083
and your mama take you
to see that movie?

47:05.257 --> 47:07.607
By the time we'd get home,
you'd hit the door

47:07.781 --> 47:10.131
and get to chopping everything
in the damn house.

47:10.305 --> 47:13.613
You chopped down our curtain...
in the room, papers flying

47:13.787 --> 47:15.441
and you just in there,
just chopping.

47:15.615 --> 47:17.269
[chuckles]:
Yeah, you remember that?

47:17.443 --> 47:20.011
And then, what, Kev-- no, Leon.

47:20.185 --> 47:21.534
Remember,
you chopped him in the neck

47:21.708 --> 47:23.797
and he rolled off
the porch out there?

47:25.755 --> 47:28.933
Couldn't tell you your name
wasn't Bruce. [chuckles]

47:30.848 --> 47:33.111
Bruce, man. The legend.
[chuckles softly]

47:34.764 --> 47:36.941
[imitating Bruce Lee]:
"Be water, my friend."

47:37.115 --> 47:38.812
[both laugh]

47:38.986 --> 47:40.205
Hey.

47:40.379 --> 47:42.598
Why don't you stay home tonight,
and we'll

47:42.772 --> 47:44.165
pop up some corn

47:44.339 --> 47:46.167
and put in the movie

47:46.341 --> 47:47.995
and take it all the way back.

47:49.997 --> 47:53.305
Just me and you,
old-school night.

47:54.872 --> 47:57.178
Spend a little time
with your old man.

47:58.963 --> 48:01.966
Huh?
What do you say?

48:24.466 --> 48:26.512
Thanks, Dad.

50:20.495 --> 50:22.976
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

50:25.196 --> 50:28.112
FRANKLIN: You mean,
let the system
destroy him...

50:28.721 --> 50:29.983
or fight it.

50:31.550 --> 50:33.465
<i>It's time
we grow past LA.</i>

50:33.639 --> 50:35.728
<i>-If we go to war...
-[whistles]</i>

50:35.902 --> 50:37.382
...we ain't gonna survive it.

50:37.556 --> 50:38.644
Let's roll.

50:40.385 --> 50:43.127
Give me some reason to believe
that we can make it out.

50:44.389 --> 50:45.651
You can't trust anyone.

50:47.087 --> 50:49.307
The shelf life in my line
of work is pretty limited.

50:55.965 --> 50:57.489
-[motorcycle engine revs]
-[barking]

50:57.663 --> 51:00.231
♪ <i>From the cradle</i>♪

51:05.323 --> 51:07.890
♪ <i>To the grave</i>♪

51:13.592 --> 51:17.161
♪ <i>We are driven</i>♪

51:19.598 --> 51:22.340
♪ <i>By the pain</i>♪
